audits are conducted at MZ to verify designs and to identify potential hazards. Recommendations may be developed as a result of these studies and as a result of equipment inspections, safety meetings, review of industry experience, technology improvements, and employee suggestions. Once formulated, recommendations are reviewed and evaluated for risk. Action items are then assigned and resourced to implement each recommendation. Communication of these action items or planned activities informs workers, the public, and other stakeholders of measurable improvements for safety that are being incorporated at MZ.

